    "narrative": "The analytical outlook for April 13 favors high-leverage spots against suspect pitching staffs. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (77.45) is the clear offensive cornerstone today, benefiting from a soft matchup against Liberatore (4.40 xERA) and favorable wind conditions that bolster his power floor. Joining him at the top of the board is **Bryson Stott** (72.46), whose profile is significantly elevated by an excellent matchup against Assad. While **Bryson Stott** typically occupies a lower spot in the order, his plate discipline against right-handed pitching provides a major boost to his daily efficiency, making him our most reliable mid-order producer. Similarly, **Geraldo Perdomo** (71.36) remains a high-value play; despite a standard platoon adjustment, he draws a +16% park factor that compensates for his placement, keeping him squarely in the strong-start tier.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Yainer Diaz**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 38.75. While his raw projections are respectable, the matchup against Kirby (3.39 xERA) creates an unforgiving ceiling, dropping him below our 40.0 \"zebra floor\" requirement. We are prioritizing the higher-upside scenarios presented by **Taylor Ward** and **Lawrence Butler**, both of whom benefit from favorable park dimensions that offset the presence of capable opposing starters. **Will Smith** remains a concern due to a pending lineup confirmation, though if he locks into the #3 spot as projected, his 60.1 score suggests he will remain a viable anchor behind the plate. We are monitoring wind patterns closely for the matchups involving **Masyn Winn** and **Jeremiah Jackson**, as their scores incorporate a +5% boost that relies on current meteorological forecasts holding through first pitch.",
